Exterior of the hostel residences in the Glebeland area of Umlazi in KwaZulu-Natal. JOHANNESBURG - The long-awaited trial of 8 suspects linked to the Glebelands killings will finally get underway at the Pietermaritzburg High Court on Monday. The so-called Glebelands eight face charges ranging from murder, attempted murder, possession of illegal firearms and ammunition. READ: 'Whistleblower' nabbed for Glebelands hostel murder Detective Bhekukwazi Mdweshu and his co-accused are believed to have run a criminal enterprise at the hostel in Umlazi, south of Durban. More than 100 people are believed to have been killed at the hostel between 2014 and 2016. The state is expected to call more than 100 witnesses.